author: Rick Coleman
title: Gladbrook-Reinbeck rolls by Wapsie Valley
text:
Gladbrook-Reinbeck rolls by Wapsie Valley - KWWL - Eastern Iowa Breaking News, Weather, Closings Member Center: Gladbrook-Reinbeck rolls by Wapsie Valley Posted: Friday Night Heroes Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> Catch all the high school football highlights during the regular season and playoffs, get live score updates and vote for the Play of the Week and the Game of the Week! More >> More >> 
In the first Rebels already up 7-0 Eric Stoakes with the carry gets it down to the one Kainen Hendricks would punch it in on the next play. 
This is where G-R had a string of three really good plays in a row... first Eric Knaack id say he has a knaack for finding the ball get the pick and takes it 70 yards for the touchdown. 
On the ensuing kickoff and check this out the ball ricochets off a Wapsie lineman and the Rebels recover. 
Following a offensive penalty an Jake Schuman drops back to pass with nothing open he scrambles left hes got some daylight 
cuts back across the field picks up a great block from a teammate... jukes out another guy 
he ran well over 100 yards on this play only 80 of them will count and superman dives into the endzone makes the score 27-0. 
later Schuman and Stoakes hook up on the screen pass and Stoakes does the rest look at that stiff arm he's in.... Rebels up 33-0 at the half. G-R rolls to a 33-14 win.
